{"title_page": "USCV-1", "text_new": "{{Infobox spaceflight\n| name               = US Crew Vehicle-1\n| image              = SpaceX Crew Dragon (More cropped).jpg\n| image_caption      = \n| insignia           = \n\n| mission_type       = Crewed mission to ISS\n| operator           = [[NASA]] / [[SpaceX]]\n| COSPAR_ID          = \n| SATCAT             = \n| mission_duration   = \n| distance_travelled = \n| orbits_completed   = \n\n| spacecraft         = \n| spacecraft_type    = [[Crew Dragon]]\n| manufacturer       = [[SpaceX]]\n| launch_mass        = {{convert|NNNN| | |abbr=on}}\n| landing_mass       = {{convert|NNNN| | |abbr=on}}\n\n| launch_date        = NET Q4 2020\n| launch_rocket      = [[Falcon 9 Full Thrust#Block 5|Falcon 9]]\n| launch_site        = [[Kennedy Space Center]], [[Launch Complex 39|LC-39A]]\n| launch_contractor  = [[SpaceX]]\n| landing_date       = 2021\n| landing_site       = Atlantic Ocean\n\n| crew_size          = 4\n| crew_members       = [[Michael S. Hopkins|Mike Hopkins]]<br/>[[Victor J. Glover|Victor Glover]]<br/>[[Soichi Noguchi]]<br/>[[Shannon Walker]]\n| crew_callsign      = \n\n| crew_photo         = \n| crew_photo_caption = \n\n| docking          = {{Infobox spaceflight/Dock\n| docking_target   = [[International Space Station|ISS]]\n| docking_type     = Dock\n| docking_port     =\n| docking_date     = \n| undocking_date   = \n| time_docked      = Six months\n}}\n| orbit_epoch       = \n| orbit_reference   = [[geocentric orbit|Geocentric]]\n| orbit_regime      = [[Low Earth orbit|Low Earth]]\n| orbit_periapsis   = \n| orbit_apoapsis    = \n| orbit_period      = \n| orbit_inclination = 51.6\u00b0 <!-- anticipated due to ISS mission --->\n| apsis             = gee\n\n| programme         = [[Commercial Crew Development|Commercial Crew Program]]\n| previous_mission  = [[Boeing Crewed Flight Test]]\n| next_mission      = [[USCV-2]]\n}}\n\n'''USCV-1''' (US Crew Vehicle-1), '''Crew-1''' or '''Crew-One''' will be the first crewed operational flight of SpaceX's [[Dragon 2|Crew Dragon]] spacecraft.<ref name=spnow>{{cite web |url=https://spacexnow.com/upcoming.php|title=Upcoming Missions|website=spacexnow.com}}</ref><ref>[https://twitter.com/VicGlover/status/1116778808428908544 Twitter message] by Victor Glover, 12 April 2019</ref> The new name for this mission will be '''SpaceX Crew Dragon-1'''.<ref>https://www.nasa.gov/specials/ccp-press-kit/main.html</ref> It is expected to launch in the second half of 2020 with a crew of four, and is planned to be the second orbital flight of Crew Dragon overall. It will transport four members of the [[Expedition 64]] crew to the [[International Space Station]].\n\n== Crew ==\n[[Michael S. Hopkins|Mike Hopkins]] and [[Victor J. Glover|Victor Glover]] were announced as the crew on 3 August 2018.<ref>{{cite web|title=Meet the Astronauts Flying SpaceX's Demo-2 |url=https://blogs.nasa.gov/commercialcrew/2018/08/03/meet-the-astronauts-assigned-to-spacexs-first-mission/|first=Marie|last=Lewis|date=3 August 2018|access-date=3 March 2019}}</ref> A [[JAXA|Japanese]] astronaut [[Soichi Noguchi]] and a third NASA astronaut, [[Shannon Walker]] were added on 31 March 2020 to the crew closer to the launch date.<ref>{{cite web|title=NASA, JAXA assign two more astronauts to second piloted Crew Dragon flight|url=https://spaceflightnow.com/2020/03/31/nasa-jaxa-assign-two-more-astronauts-to-second-piloted-crew-dragon-flight/|first=|last=|date=31 March 2020|access-date=1 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n{{Spaceflight crew\n|terminology    = Astronaut\n\n|position1      = Commander\n|crew1_up       = {{Flagicon|USA}} [[Michael S. Hopkins]]\n|flights1_up    = Second\n|agency1_up     = [[NASA]]\n|expedition1_up = [[Expedition 64]]\n\n|position2      = Pilot\n|crew2_up       = {{Flagicon|USA}} [[Victor J. Glover]]\n|flights2_up    = First\n|agency2_up     = [[NASA]]\n|expedition2_up = [[Expedition 64]]\n\n|position3      = Mission Specialist 1\n|crew3_up       = {{Flagicon|Japan}} [[Soichi Noguchi]]\n|flights3_up    = Third\n|agency3_up     = [[JAXA]]\n|expedition3_up = [[Expedition 64]]\n\n|position4      = Mission Specialist 2\n|crew4_up       = {{Flagicon|USA}} [[Shannon Walker]]\n|flights4_up    = Second\n|agency4_up     = [[NASA]]\n|expedition4_up = [[Expedition 64]] \n}}\n\n== Back-up crew==\n{{Spaceflight crew\n|terminology    = Astronaut\n\n|position1      = Commander\n|crew1_up       = {{Flagicon|USA}} [[Kjell N. Lindgren]] \n|flights1_up    = \n|agency1_up     = [[NASA]]\n|expedition1_up = \n\n|position2      = Pilot\n|crew2_up       = {{Flagicon|USA}} TBA\n|flights2_up    = \n|agency2_up     = [[NASA]]\n|expedition2_up = \n\n|position3      = Mission Specialist 1\n|crew3_up       = TBA\n|flights3_up    = \n|agency3_up     = \n|expedition3_up = \n\n|position4      = Mission Specialist 2\n|crew4_up       = TBA\n|flights4_up    = \n|agency4_up     = \n|expedition4_up = \n}}\n\n== See also ==\n* [[Boeing CST-100 Starliner]]\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Portal|Spaceflight}}\n{{Manned ISS flights}}\n{{Dragon spaceflights}}\n{{Falcon rocket launches}}\n{{Future spaceflights}}\n\n[[Category:SpaceX Dragon]]\n[[Category:2020 in spaceflight]]\n[[Category:SpaceX payloads contracted by NASA]]\n[[Category:SpaceX human spaceflights]]\n[[Category:Future human spaceflights]]\n\n{{space-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox spaceflight\n| name               = SpaceX Crew Dragon-1\n| image              = SpaceX Crew Dragon (More cropped).jpg\n| image_caption      = \n| insignia           = \n\n| mission_type       = Crewed mission to ISS\n| operator           = [[NASA]] / [[SpaceX]]\n| COSPAR_ID          = \n| SATCAT             = \n| mission_duration   = \n| distance_travelled = \n| orbits_completed   = \n\n| spacecraft         = \n| spacecraft_type    = [[Crew Dragon]]\n| manufacturer       = [[SpaceX]]\n| launch_mass        = {{convert|NNNN| | |abbr=on}}\n| landing_mass       = {{convert|NNNN| | |abbr=on}}\n\n| launch_date        = NET Q4 2020\n| launch_rocket   